**MIXA-010 is complete.** The Go engine lifecycle was already fully implemented — the only issue was a TypeScript readonly type mismatch in the engine store that was causing the typecheck to fail. Fixed by updating `updateStatus` to accept `ReadonlyArray` matching the preload's `as const` assertion.

All acceptance criteria verified:
1. Electron main spawns Go engine binary on app start
2. Binary path resolved for both packaged and dev modes
3. gRPC client connects with retry logic (5 retries)
4. Health check polling every 10 seconds
5. Auto-restart on crash with exponential backoff (max 3 retries)
6. Graceful shutdown via SIGTERM with SIGKILL fallback
7. Engine status exposed to renderer via IPC + tRPC
8. Status indicator in browser chrome (colored dot + "Fenix" label)
9. Logs captured and forwarded to renderer
10. Works in both dev and production modes

All backpressure checks pass (typecheck, lint, build, go vet, go test). Committed as `720f6e9`.